cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on enhancing the performance of convolutional neural networks for image classification tasks. It also involves deep learning (cs.LG) techniques and neural network optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for improving the representational ability of binary convolutional networks, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the experiments involve image datasets, which could also place the paper under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
